# Alias @a: rooting rules
# Scopes the source behind deterministic, current-worktree-first @a: alias
# resolution and its output: the alias resolver seam + seed guard + --job
# worktree rerooting (manager.go), the rule-line resolution seams (resolve.go,
# resolver_context.go), the AST attribution + zero-match warning + relativize
# (resolver.go), the concept @concept: line-number threading (rules.go), and the
# `cx list` absolute-path command layer (cmd/list.go). Changes to any of these
# should trigger the cx-alias-rooting E2E scenario, which drives `cx list` from
# an XDG multi-worktree fixture and asserts current-worktree preference,
# absolute output, --job worktree rooting, and no spurious zero-match warning.
# Paths are relative to the cx repo root.

pkg/context/manager.go
pkg/context/resolve.go
pkg/context/resolver.go
pkg/context/resolver_context.go
pkg/context/rules.go
cmd/list.go
tests/e2e/scenarios_alias_rooting.go
